en_72604_0	Government source state that the Western and Southern Provincial Councils are scheduled to be dissolved during the month of December.
en_72604_1	Accordingly the two provincial councils are most likely to be dissolved between the 18th and 26th of December.
en_72604_2	According to the Elections Act the elections commissioner has to issue to gazette notice calling for nominations within 14 days of the dissolution of a provincial council.
en_72604_3	Thus the gazette notice calling for nominations will most likely be issued within the first week of January.
en_72604_4	Hence the election will be held between 5 to 7 weeks from the date the nominations are called for.
en_72604_5	Government sources stated that accordingly the election for the Western and Southern Provincial Councils will be held on either the 1st or 8th of March next year.
en_72604_6	The election for the two provincial councils will be held according to the 2013 voters list.
en_72604_7	Meanwhile, reports state that the government has turned its attention towards dissolving the Uva Provincial Council along with the Western and Southern Provincial Councils.
en_72604_8	A government spokesperson stated that a decision in this regard will be taken during the Central Working Committee meeting of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party which will be held before the party general convention.
en_72604_9	Although the SLFP general convention is scheduled to be held on the 18th of this month, that may change due to an issue with the scheduled location.
